President Biden has declared a major disaster in the state of Alabama following severe storms, straight-line winds, and tornadoes on January 12, 2023. This declaration allows for federal funding to assist individuals in Autauga and Dallas counties. The assistance may include grants for temporary housing and home repairs, low-cost loans for uninsured property losses, and other programs to aid in recovery. Federal funding is also available for emergency work and hazard mitigation measures. Kevin A. Wallace, Sr. has been named the Federal Coordinating Officer for recovery operations in the affected areas. Damage assessments are still ongoing, and additional areas may receive assistance once assessments are completed. Residents and business owners can apply for assistance through various channels, such as the FEMA website, hotline, or app. For further information, the FEMA News Desk can be contacted.